{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/flash-video-the-solution/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"James Ford","author":"James Ford"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"1c7b11a8-2660-5de3-89de-e8a2dd662ea3","html":"<p>Working with a lot of Flash video (.flv) I'm acutely aware of the lack in decent, standalone FLV Players. Sure, there's a few out there, but not many that are decent. I have used <a href=\"http://www.softpedia.com/progScreenshots/FLV-Player-Screenshot-27852.html\" title=\"Open this link in a new window.\">FLV Player 1.3.3</a>, but it's not up to much when you're trying to preview or edit files. Adobe's own <a href=\"http://www.adobe.com/products/flash/flashpro/productinfo/encoder/\" title=\"Open this link in a new window.\">Flash Video Encoder</a> is worse than id've thought it would be. You can only encode once, and you can't decode, edit or view the files afterwards. We have been promised the arrival of the <a href=\"http://labs.adobe.com/wiki/index.php/Media_Player\" title=\"Open this link in a new window.\">Adobe Media Player</a>, but that's no comfort until it actually materializes.</p>\n<p>By far the best solution for playing Flash Video so far is the <a href=\"http://www.richapps.de/?p=48\" title=\"Open this link in a new window.\">RichFLV 2</a> - an Apollo-based desktop FLV Player. It's in Alpha stage of production, (isn't everything nowadays?) but it's already looking far more promising than any competition.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 128px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6761dd7ad159e15e308283e6fd4d5fb5/1c250/adobe-apollo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Adobe Apollo CS3\"\n        title=\"Adobe Apollo CS3\"\n        src=\"/static/6761dd7ad159e15e308283e6fd4d5fb5/1c250/adobe-apollo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6761dd7ad159e15e308283e6fd4d5fb5/1c250/adobe-apollo.png 128w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 128px) 100vw, 128px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"Flash Video - the Solution?","date":"May 28, 2007","tags":["flash","air","tools"],"url":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/6761dd7ad159e15e308283e6fd4d5fb5/ae1fe/adobe-apollo.png","srcSet":"/static/6761dd7ad159e15e308283e6fd4d5fb5/ae1fe/adobe-apollo.png 128w","sizes":"(max-width: 128px) 100vw, 128px"}},"colors":{"vibrant":"#E4120C","darkVibrant":"#7F0B04","lightVibrant":"#EC8484","muted":"#BA6561","darkMuted":"#940D05","lightMuted":"#D5A2A2"}},"description":null,"image_credit":null}}},"pageContext":{"prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/kuler-desktop-released/","tags":["air","colour","downloadable-applications","kuler","resources","tools"],"title":"Kuler Desktop released!","date":"2007-05-28T13:25:54.000Z","description":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.25,"src":"/static/b9d72830a02e8eb6a1f7c3c60f599c4c/01f29/kulerdesktop.jpg","srcSet":"/static/b9d72830a02e8eb6a1f7c3c60f599c4c/5f64f/kulerdesktop.jpg 158w,\n/static/b9d72830a02e8eb6a1f7c3c60f599c4c/981d4/kulerdesktop.jpg 315w,\n/static/b9d72830a02e8eb6a1f7c3c60f599c4c/01f29/kulerdesktop.jpg 480w","sizes":"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px"}}}}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/rss-bling-or-no-bling/","tags":["design","rss-tag"],"tit